          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. The production volume is based on the production volume of clay roof tiles in Europe (RER dataset) and the nominal GDP 2019 for EC and Europe. It's assumed the same share between glazed and conventional clay roof tiles.
According to EuroStat, the production of clay roofing tiles in the European Union in 2019 was 2'577'423'791 units [1]. In Europe the assumed average weight per unit is 4 kg [2]. The nominal (current) GDP of the EU in 2019 was 15'693'403'575'262.4 US$ and in EC was 108'108'009'000 US$ [3].
Sources: 
[1] "Non-refractory clay roofing tiles", EUROPEAN UNION (28), PRODQNT.
Industry, trade and services&gt;Statistics on the production of manufactured foods (prom)&gt;Sold production, exports and imports (ds-056120). Retrieved from: https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/view/DS-056120__custom_7772056/default/table?lang=en
[2] ecoinvent v2 Report 7, Buildings, Part IV, p. 25. Presumed weight per tile: 4 kg.
[3] https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/NY.GDP.MKTP.CD
</productionVolumeComment>
